* Instance Pools
** What it does
***_ Keeps idle VMs ready
***_ Reduces cluster startup time
***_ From minutes → under 1 minute
** Configuration
*** Min idle instances
****_ Warm instances always available
****_ Match concurrent cluster needs
*** Max capacity
****_ Controls costs
****_ Fair resource distribution
*** Idle auto termination
****_ Removes excess idle instances
****_ Reduces idle cost
** Preload Databricks Runtime
***_ Preinstalled runtime on idle VMs
***_ Near-instant cluster launches
** Cost model
***_ Pay for idle VMs (not DBU)
***_ Justified by frequent cluster use
** Spot instances for workers
***_ Reduce cost significantly
***_ On-demand for driver nodes
** Less relevant with serverless
***_ Serverless starts faster
***_ No idle capacity needed
@endmindmap
